Dear MESD School Community,

Please see today’s executive order and school opening plan from Governor Ducey and Supt. Hoffman. We are pleased that this plan is aligned to our district’s Return to Learn plan recently shared with our stakeholders and governing board. We greatly appreciate the support of our local and state authorities in allowing for local decision-making. As of today’s announcement, our opening date for in-person and online learning pathways remains August 17, 2020.

The Plan
https://azgovernor.gov/governor/news/2020/07/governor-ducey-announces-additional-dollars-flexibility-and-clarity-arizona

Executive Order
https://azgovernor.gov/sites/default/files/executive_order_2020-51.pdf

Thank you,

Dr. Aspasia Angelou
Superintendent
Nadaburg Unified School District No. 81 & Morristown Elementary District No. 75

post_text:
Morristown Elementary school District Pathways To Learn Plan for 2020/2021 School Year

Goals Of The Return To Learn Plan

¡Encourage student and staff health and safety

¡Build relationships and active partnerships with families

¡Provide quality learning environments for both in-person and online models

¡Personalize experiences to meet the unique needs of students and families

Please take the time to review the Power Point presented at the board meeting.
(Power point included)

Return to learning for all students will be August 17, 2020. Morristown Elementary School District students and families will have options for learning. We are asking all families to please read the description for each learning pathway, fill out the form and select the pathway that best fits your student’s needs and the needs of your family:
https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/mesdreturn

Dear Parents, Students, Teachers and Staff:

Please note that our start date has been pushed back to August 17th, 2020, according to the following:

Governor Ducey’s Executive Order

https://azgovernor.gov/governor/news/2020/06/governor-ducey-takes-further-action-reverse-covid-19-spread-arizona

In-person learning will not open until August 17th, 2020. We are collecting feedback from parents, teachers and staff to formulate the best options for keeping our school community safe and healthy when we reopen in the fall.

Thank you for taking some time to give us feedback on your concerns and preferences.

Dr. Aspasia Angelou
Superintendent

Nadaburg Unified School District No. 81
aangelou@nadaburgsd.org
Morristown Elementary School District No. 75

post_text:
Need library books? We got you covered!

Parents, Ms. Maben will be onsite and available to check out books to students so that they can continue their reading efforts at home.

You or your child(ren) can check out her inventory by looking through her catalog at the following link:

https://morristowneld75.follettdestiny.com/common/welcome.jsp?context=saas83_0200311

See a book you want? Just email Ms. Maben at fmaben@morristowneld75.org the title and author and she will get it checked out to your child and email back when it is ready.

Books can be picked up at the school with other work, or if your child is participating in the grab and go lunch and breakfast at one of our bus stops, we are happy to send it in the van with our lunch crew. Please return books in the same manner.

Also, please try to return any library books your child(ren) have at home through one of the two above options.

Please call our office at 623-546-5100 or email Ms. Maben with any questions.

post_text:
Please read the following in regards to the cancellation of the FREE PHYSICALS.

Hello Community Health Fair Partners,



The CDC has issued temporary guidelines for organizers responsible for planning community events to take preventative precautions during this emerging public health threat. As a leading health care provider, Wickenburg Community Hospital & Clinics is rescheduling current public events until new information is made available by the Centers for Disease Control.



This includes our Community Health Fair w/Free Sports Physicals.



Please inform students and parents that a new date for the Student Athlete Physicals is forthcoming. In the interim, students eligible for Annual Wellness Checks through their insurance plans may receive a sports physical at no additional fee through our Community Clinics in Wickenburg, Congress or Wittmann. The clinics’ phone number is 928-668-1833, if they would like to schedule and our team can verify with the insurance is they are eligible for the wellness visit.

Maricopa County School Superintendent's Office
June 19, 2019 at 3:25 PM ·

Teachers from across Maricopa County joined Maricopa County School Superintendent Steve Watson in an all-day professional development at Palo Verde Generating Station this past week. In addition to learning about nuclear energy, they had hands-on learning sessions about buoyancy, relative humidity, centrifugal pumps, speed ratios, DC currents and chaos and predictability. #teacherresources #APS #nuclearenergy #STEMeducation

Thank you for your patience during this time.

Dr. Gregory Sackos

Maricopa teachers!!! Here is a chance for another giveaway....

Several local STEM education agencies put together a survey in order to provide better support to teachers.
